<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,871,1162]" pageId="14" pageNumber="47">
Shrubs 0.5–2.0 m tall. This species differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1074,985,1010]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrciaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[956,1074,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="47">Myrciaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having shorter leaves (1.5– 3.0 cm long), a sulcate midvein on the adaxial lamina surface, and shorter bracteoles.
</paragraph>
